description:
&lt;p&gt;A vacancy has arisen within Gastrointestinal Surgery for a Band 7 GI Surgical Care Practitioner. You will need to be flexible and adaptable with excellent communication and organisational skills and most importantly, unlimited enthusiasm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will be Band 7 already qualified to assist in theatre and undertake independent outpatient clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is also open to any staff applying as a trainee at Band 6. Trainees will undergo a training programme led by the Senior Surgical Care Practitioner. On completion of this training and evidence of competency this role will progress to a Band 7.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will be a full time post. Out of hours work may be required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to work in pleasant surroundings for a progressive employer which actively promotes education and training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have excellent communication skills and a good knowledge and understanding of clinical standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nicola Devlin, Senior Surgical Care Practitioner (07557499751) ndevlin@nhs.net, or Melanie Feldman Speciality Lead for Colorectal Surgery, Karen Cock Colorectal Consultant Nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
